-- NBA-Leading Spurs Beat Kings 130-102, Lose Top Scorer Parker
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-03-02T06:13:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-02/nba-leading-spurs-beat-kings-130-102-lose-top-scorer-parker.html
The National Basketball Association-
leading San Antonio Spurs lost top scorer Tony Parker in their
130-102 defeat of the Sacramento Kings.  Parker suffered an ankle sprain on a drive to the basket
with four minutes, 40 seconds left in the third quarter. He was
helped off the court after falling to the ground and grabbing
his leg.  DeJuan Blair scored 16 points, Danny Green had 15 points,
Kawhi Leonard and Tiago Splitter each added 14 and Parker, Tim Duncan and Matt Bonner scored 13 points apiece last night at
AT&T Center in San Antonio,  Texas .  Marcus Thornton had 22 points and Isaiah Thomas tallied 18
for the Kings.  The Spurs (46-14) lead the NBA, two games ahead of the
Miami Heat (42-14) and 26 games in front of the Kings (20-40).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
